<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,474,967]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,497,654,679]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[504,725,654,679]" class="Reptilia" family="Dactyloidae" genus="Anolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis box="[504,725,654,679]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Anolis meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in the Brazilian Cerrado and Pantanal, occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[186,254,690,715]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[320,403,690,715]" name="Bolivia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[424,499,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1722,1744]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,195,1679]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,195,1701]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution of examined material of Anolis chrysolepis, A. dissimilis and A. meridionalis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/234982/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Fig. 
<number box="[482,499,691,715]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[561,632,690,715]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it is known from the states of Maranhão, Piauí, Bahia, Tocantins, Rondônia, Mato Grosso, Mato Grosso do Sul, Goiás, Minas Gerais, São Paulo, and in the Distrito Federal. It was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[328,433,763,787]" name="Paraguay" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, from where there are some recent records (
<bibRefCitation author="Langstroth" box="[928,1118,762,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Langstroth, R. P. (2006) Notas sobre Anolis meridionalis Boettger, 1885 (Squamata: Iguania: Polychrotidae) en Bolivia y comentarios sobre Anolis steinbachi. Kempffiana, 2, 154 - 172." type="journal article" year="2006">
Langstroth 
<number box="[1058,1118,762,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Motte" box="[1130,1394,762,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Motte, M. &amp; Cacciali, P. (2009) Descripcion de un neotipo para Anolis meridionalis Boettger, 1885 (Sauria: Polychrotidae). Cuadernos de Herpetologia, 23, 19 - 24." type="journal article" year="2009">
Motte &amp; Cacciali 
<number box="[1333,1394,763,787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In Amazonia it occurs in enclaves of open vegetation in northwestern Mato Grosso and southern Rondônia states, in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,222,834,859]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[417,503,834,859]" name="Bolivia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[515,736,834,859]" class="Reptilia" family="Dactyloidae" genus="Anolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis box="[515,736,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Anolis meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is predominantly terrestrial and diurnal, inhabits open grassy habitats (Nogueira 
<emphasis box="[378,441,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[454,514,871,895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2009.0">2009</number>
), gallery forests (
<bibRefCitation author="Langstroth" box="[726,923,870,895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Langstroth, R. P. (2006) Notas sobre Anolis meridionalis Boettger, 1885 (Squamata: Iguania: Polychrotidae) en Bolivia y comentarios sobre Anolis steinbachi. Kempffiana, 2, 154 - 172." type="journal article" year="2006">
Langstroth 
<number box="[863,923,870,895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), rocky outcrops (
<bibRefCitation author="Uetanabaro" box="[1143,1424,870,895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Uetanabaro, M., Souza, F. L., Landgref-Filho, P., Beda, A. F. &amp; Brandao, R. A. (2007) Anfibios e repteis do Parque Nacional da Serra da Bodoquena, Mato Grosso do Sul, Brasil. Biota Neotropica, 7, 279 - 289. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1676 - 06032007000300030" type="journal article" year="2007">
Uetanabaro 
<emphasis box="[1288,1350,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1364,1424,871,895]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), seasonally flooded open areas (Chaco—Souza 
<emphasis box="[674,730,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[736,796,907,931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2010.0">2010</number>
), and perianthropic areas (
<bibRefCitation author="Vaz-Silva" box="[1088,1327,906,931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Vaz-Silva, W., Guedes, A. G., Azevedo-Silva, P. L., Gontijo, F. F., Barbosa, R. S., Aloisio, G. R. &amp; Oliveira, F. C. G. (2007) Herpetofauna, Espora hydroelectric power plant, state of Goias, Brazil. Check List, 3, 338 - 345." type="journal article" year="2007">
Vaz-Silva 
<emphasis box="[1205,1261,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1267,1327,907,931]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), where it is found on the ground, and on lower vegetation (lower than 
<quantity box="[831,915,943,967]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="m" value="1.0">1 meter</quantity>
high—Vitt 
<number box="[1049,1108,943,967]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1991.0">1991</number>
a).
</paragraph>
